# CSS Styling Rules

## Base Configuration

Always set the HTML font-size to 62.5% for easy REM calculations (1rem = 10px):

```css
html {
  font-size: 62.5%; /* 1rem = 10px */
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: inherit;
}
```

---

## REM Units

Use REM units for sizing, spacing, and typography. Never use pixels except for borders.

```css
/* ❌ BAD */
.button {
  font-size: 16px;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  margin: 15px;
}

/* ✅ GOOD */
.button {
  font-size: 1.6rem; /* 16px */
  padding: 1rem 2rem; /* 10px 20px */
  margin: 1.5rem; /* 15px */
  border: 1px solid #ccc; /* Pixels OK for borders */
}
```

